at will be,","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Ecc:1:10","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Ecc","bookOrder":20,"chapter":1,"verse":10,"text":"Can one say about anything,","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Ecc:1:11","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Ecc","bookOrder":20,"chapter":1,"verse":11,"text":"There is no remembrance of those who came before;","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Ecc:1:12","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Ecc","bookOrder":20,"chapter":1,"verse":12,"text":"I, the Teacher, have been king over Israel in Jerusalem.","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Ecc:1:13","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Ecc","bookOrder":20,"chapter":1,"verse":13,"text":"I applied my mind to examine and explore through wisdom all that is done under heaven. God has given people this miserable task to keep them occupied.","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Ecc:1:14","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Ecc","bookOrder":20,"chapter":1,"verse":14,"text":"I have seen all the things that are done under the sun and have found everything to be futile, a pursuit of the wind.","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Ecc:1:15","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Ecc","bookOrder":20,"chapter":1,"verse":15,"text":"What is crooked cannot be straightened;","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Ecc:1:16","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Ecc","bookOrder":20,"chapter":1,"verse":16,"text":"I said to myself, “See, I have amassed wisdom far beyond all those who were over Jerusalem before me, and my mind has thoroughly grasped wisdom and knowledge.”","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Ecc:1:17","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Ecc","bookOrder":20,"chapter":1,"ve